# SEO & Performance

## SEO in Sanity

Every page has an `seo` object field with: `metaTitle`, `metaDescription`, `ogImage`, `canonicalUrl`, `siteName`.
Site-wide defaults live in `siteSettings.seo`; page-level SEO overrides them.

Fallback chain in pages:
```
pageSeo?.metaTitle ?? page?.title ?? siteSeo?.metaTitle ?? "Practice Porter"
```

## Required meta tags

`Layout.astro` renders these in `<head>`:
- `<title>` from the SEO chain above
- `<meta name="description">` if present
- `<meta property="og:title">` and `og:description`
- `<meta property="og:image">` and `twitter:image` from ogImage asset URL
- `<meta name="generator">` (Astro built-in)
- `<link rel="icon">` (SVG + ICO)

When adding new pages or content types, always ensure SEO fields are included.

## Performance rules

- Images from Sanity CDN — use asset URL with transformations, not base64
- No `client:load` on components that don't need interactivity — prefer `client:visible` or `client:idle` for below-the-fold content
- Fonts: Inter via `@fontsource-variable/inter` (self-hosted), Playfair via Google Fonts `@import`
- Film grain overlay (`body::after`) is `pointer-events: none` with fixed positioning
- `useCdn: false` in Sanity config because SSR fetches fresh content per request

## Lighthouse targets

- Performance: 90+
- Accessibility: 95+
- SEO: 100
- Best Practices: 95+
